Tranquillity first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Tranquillity had a population of 805. The population density was {{convert|1,304.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Tranquillity was 183 (22.7%) [[White Americans|White]], 2 (0.2%) [[African Americans|African American]], 5 (0.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (0.1%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 401 (49.8%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 213 (26.5%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 694 persons (86.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Tranquillity CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0680266 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 231 households, out of which 95 (41.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 128 (55.4%) were married-couple households, 9 (3.9%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 51 (22.1%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 43 (18.6%) had a male householder with no partner present. 34 households (14.7%) were one person, and 14 (6.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.48.<ref name=DP1/> There were 181 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (78.4% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Tranquillity CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0680266 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 253 people (31.4%) under the age of 18, 83 people (10.3%) aged 18 to 24, 199 people (24.7%) aged 25 to 44, 158 people (19.6%) aged 45 to 64, and 112 people (13.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 30.5{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 102.3 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 248 housing units at an average density of {{convert|401.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 231 (93.1%) were occupied. Of these, 126 (54.5%) were owner-occupied, and 105 (45.5%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0680266|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715033557/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0680266|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Tranquillity CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Tranquillity had a population of 799. The population density was {{convert|1,294.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Tranquillity was 504 (63.1%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 9 (1.1%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 13 (1.6%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2 (0.3%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 251 (31.4%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 20 (2.5%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 637 persons (79.7%).

The Census reported that 799 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 229 households, out of which 120 (52.4%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 141 (61.6%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 21 (9.2%) had a female householder with no husband present, 20 (8.7%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 15 (6.6%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 38 households (16.6%) were made up of individuals, and 13 (5.7%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 3.49.  There were 182 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (79.5% of all households); the average family size was 3.98.

The population age distribution is 267 people (33.4%) under the age of 18, 55 people (6.9%) aged 18 to 24, 206 people (25.8%) aged 25 to 44, 177 people (22.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 94 people (11.8%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 32.7 years. For every 100 females, there were 106.5 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 103.1 males.

There were 255 housing units at an average density of {{convert|413.0|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 229 were occupied, of which 145 (63.3%) were owner-occupied, and 84 (36.7%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 2.0%; the rental vacancy rate was 13.3%.  478 people (59.8% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 321 people (40.2%) lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, the median income for a household in the CDP was $42,857, and the median income for a family was $60,208. Males had a median income of $29,250 versus $17,222 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $13,128.  About 12.2% of families and 7.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 5.2% of those under age 18 and 17.7% of those age 65 or over.

